# EduForge — SaaS LMS Platform Builder

## What is EduForge?
EduForge is a multi-tenant SaaS platform that lets users build and launch their own online learning platforms (called "Agencies"). Think Teachable + Webflow combined.

## Architecture in one sentence
A Next.js 15 monorepo where `middleware.ts` routes subdomains to tenant pages, and GrapesJS powers the drag-and-drop page builder.

## User types
- **Super Admin** — manages the entire platform (templates, plans, all tenants)
- **Agency Owner** — creates and manages their learning platform (the tenant)
- **Trainer** — creates courses within an agency
- **Student** — enrolls in and consumes courses

## Key URLs
- `app.eduforge.com/dashboard` — Agency Owner dashboard
- `app.eduforge.com/builder/[agencyId]` — Drag & Drop builder
- `ahmed-academy.eduforge.com` — Public-facing agency site
- `app.eduforge.com/admin` — Super Admin panel

## Monorepo structure
- `apps/web/` — The Next.js 15 application (everything is here)
- `packages/types/` — Shared TypeScript interfaces
- `packages/api-client/` — All API calls (never call the backend directly from components)
- `packages/builder-core/` — GrapesJS configuration and custom blocks
- `packages/config/` — Shared ESLint, TypeScript, Tailwind configs
